            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Macedonia and Achaia",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Shortly after 146 b.c., all Greece south of Macedonia and Epirus was formed into a Roman province under the name of Achaia, and Macedonia with Epirus into another province called Macedonia. ",
        "children": []
      }
